Context:
    My significant other is in the final year of her Emergency Medicine (EM) training at the Mayo Clinic in Rochester, MN. She is starting her job search for an Emergency Medical Physcian job following the completion of her Residency Program in June 2027.
Job Criteria:
    Job title: Emergency Medical Physcian
        EXCLUDE: Midlevel APPs such as Physician Assistants and Nurse Practitioners
        EXCLUDE: Medical Director roles
        EXCLUDE: EM Fellowship roles
    Location Prefences:
        California (Within 30-40 minutes of the California coast, or within the California Bay Area with a preference for North, South, and West Bay, but east bay will be considered. Highest preference for Bay Area and San Diego)
        Colorado (Denver Boulder Area but open to others)
        Bozeman MT
        Connecticut (Near Stamford, CT)
        Massachusetts (Near and South of Boston, MA with a preference for the coast)
        Note: Will consider other locations on the east coast if the pay is competitive (>$400k)
    Minimum Salary:
        $300,000
    Target Salary:
        $350,000-$400,000
    Job Type:
        Full Time employment with benefits
        Do not include locum tenens jobs
        NO NOCTURNE JOBS (NO OVERNIGHT SHIFTS)
    Insutition Type:
        Academic Medical Center
        Trauma Center (Tier I Preferred)
        Private Hospital Group
        No HCA hospitals
        Prefer Level I, II, and III hospitals within one hour of a major metropolitan area
Goal:
    Create a program that will scrape the internet for Emergency Medical Physician jobs that meet the above criteria.
    The program should output to a live dashboard with a sharable URL
    The dashboard should display jobs that meet the criteria, including the job title, location, salary, and institution type, and a link to the job posting.
    The dashboard should attempt to find the hiring manager or recruiter for the job posting and provide an email address for the hiring manager or recruiter.
    The dashboard should cross reference for individuals working at that institutions with a history at Mayo Clinic and flag those as high warm leads.
    The program should also output a list of jobs that do not meet the criteria, including the reason why they do not meet the criteria.
    The program should be able to be run on a daily, weekly, and custom basis to check for new jobs.
